Author: brlewis
Content:
Cheating would be putting an open paren at the top of the file, a close paren at the bottom, and implementing it in Scheme as

Author: Tichy
Content: I don't think that Java programmer was up to scratch, although admittedly Java won't get as short as Ruby. I would count that readline construct of Ruby as kind of cheating, though. It's a specialized feature that doesn't say much about the brevity of Ruby in general.
